# hs-messaging-service

Go HTTP service using Echo v5 + GORM + Postgres. Entry point is `cmd/api/main.go`.

## Layered architecture (strict)

`routes -> handlers -> service -> repository -> domain`

- Handlers (`internal/api/handlers`): parse request, call service, return JSON. No DB calls.
- Services (`internal/service`): business logic and validation. No Echo types.
- Repositories (`internal/repository/postgres`): GORM queries only. No business rules.
- Domain (`internal/domain`): structs with GORM + JSON tags. No behavior.

## Workflow for new endpoints

1. Add or update a domain model (register in `AutoMigrate` in `repository/postgres/connection.go`).
2. Repository method -> service method -> handler -> route registration.
3. Wire the handler + service + repo in `cmd/api/main.go`.

## Commands

- Run: `docker compose up -d && go run ./cmd/api`
- Check: `go vet ./... && gofmt -l .`
- Test: `go test ./...`

Never commit `.env` or real secrets.
